## Roles and Responsibilities of a entry level Software Engineer
- Developing Solutiions
- Testing and finalising solutions
- Fixing errors
- Coordinating and communicating witha team and other stakeholders
- Learning and teaching new technologies and skills

### Developing Solutions
- Understand the task that is being asked of you.
- Review existing documentation on the topic (e.g. online or inside the company).
- Propose an approach to solve the task.
- Ask questions as needed to clarify task.
- Use coding best practices and design patterns (e.g. naming conventions, track changes, version control, consistency throughout code, make code self-explanatory).
- Write code needed for solution.
- Reuse code when appropriate.

### Testing and finalising solutions
- Use a DevOps approach to make code reviews along the coding process.
- Have knowledge of/be willing to self-teach about tests (e.g. Unit testing).
- Track code production (e.g. Application Performance Management or(APM) to track systems and discover error).
- Test solutions across different softwares.

### Fixing Errors
- Locate the code that contains error independently or with support from colleagues.
- Test the functionality that has an error.
-  Understand the technical details of the current error.
-  Test the solution is working correctly.
-  Test everything that can be affected by the error(whole system).

